{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":35925,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-10T14:13:43.727Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Modanung\" data-post=\"15\" data-topic=\"5913\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/40/2706_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Modanung:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe subjective validity of your statement also depends on what one considers to be ‚Äúfunctional changes \u003cem\u003ein\u003c/em\u003e Urho‚Äù. It is in the lightweight bare-bones nature of Urho for its functionality to expand in the peripherals.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSaid it before. If you cannot implement some simple task without deep changes in the engine, it‚Äôs not really ‚Äúlightweight‚Äù, it‚Äôs ‚Äúmissing features‚Äù. Or outright missing features, e.g. no networking in Web builds. I don‚Äôt mean Urho cannot be used. It totally can and Urho community prove it. But it would be lie to say that Urho don‚Äôt miss anything.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, only a person who never looked at Urho renderer code can call it ‚Äúlightweight‚Äù. It‚Äôs complicated as hell. Ever looked at View.cpp/Batch.cpp?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-10T18:31:40.759Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":28,"reads":66,"readers_count":65,"score":158.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5916,"topic_slug":"improving-the-render-pipeline","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/about-rbfx-and-urho3d/5913/16","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"About rbfx and Urho3D","clicks":0},{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/about-rbfx-and-urho3d/5913/18","internal":true,"reflection":true,"title":"About rbfx and Urho3D","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":35940,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-10T15:35:07.633Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Eugene\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"5916\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/40/902_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e Eugene:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAlso, only a person who never looked at Urho renderer code can call it ‚Äúlightweight‚Äù. It‚Äôs complicated as hell. Ever looked at View.cpp/Batch.cpp?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSome things like the logic for pingponging postprocess buffers is definitely not clear or lightweight, instead it‚Äôs just very hardcoded and there‚Äôs an element of ‚Äúmagic‚Äù to it, which is not nice to have.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne thing which I pondered as a simpler replacement was having high-level helper operations (ie. collect visible objects, collect light interactions, render a collection of objects‚Ä¶) in the Renderer which could be used to make your custom render process in code, somewhat like Unity‚Äôs Scriptable Render Pipelines are today. Back when I worked on it, Turso3D went a bit into this direction, but didn‚Äôt get very far.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-10T18:31:40.856Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":1,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":66,"readers_count":65,"score":33.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5916,"topic_slug":"improving-the-render-pipeline","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":35942,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-10T15:55:53.050Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"cadaver\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"5916\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/40/3_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e cadaver:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne thing which I pondered as a simpler replacement was having high-level helper operations (ie. collect visible objects, collect light interactions, render a collection of objects‚Ä¶) in the Renderer which could be used to make your custom render process in code, somewhat like Unity‚Äôs Scriptable Render Pipelines are today\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis sounds quite close to what I meant here:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Eugene\" data-post=\"74\" data-topic=\"5872\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/40/902_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/migration-from-custom-container-library-to-augmented-eastl/5872/74\"\u003eMigration from custom container library to augmented EASTL\u003c/a\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI have several ideas how to change renderer, but I will not make any plans or promises until I confirm they will work out well.\u003cbr\u003e\nI want to try one radical approach, but it will require huge commitment of effort and therefore you will not get any updates in the nearest months about it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSince you are here, maybe you can share some thoughts?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere are a lot of issues (or so I think) in the renderer.\u003cbr\u003e\nGoing from top to bottom:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col start=\"0\"\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHard to extend and configure render paths, need an instance for each permutation. E.g. if I want to choose between sRGB and RGB with just a flag, or I want optional GBuffer layer for Deferred, I need to clone RP. We have it now with e.g. Forward/ForwardDepth\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThere is no per-view-per-drawable state, essentially making things like smooth LOD transitions very hard to implement in multi-view use cases.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDrawables store a lot of temporary View-specific data used only in rendering.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eVertex lights fall back into pixel lights (lolwat) instead of spherical harmonics (cannot really blame Urho because there were no SH back then, but still an issue)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHardcoded vertex and pixel shader permutations, missing automatic shader defines. E.g. I want shader to automatically get defines like \u003ccode\u003ePASS_LITBASE\u003c/code\u003e, \u003ccode\u003eTEXTURE_DIFFUSE\u003c/code\u003e or \u003ccode\u003eINPUT_NORMAL\u003c/code\u003e. If we had it, there would be no need to have 100 techniques for each permutation.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAlmost zero caching of computations done in View/Batch.cpp, even if result is the same for consequent frames.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUniform Buffers are used in the way opposite to how they are supposed to be used. No wonder they are slower on OpenGL and are disabled there.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-10T18:31:40.888Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":62,"readers_count":61,"score":37.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":5916,"topic_slug":"improving-the-render-pipeline","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":2,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/migration-from-custom-container-library-to-augmented-eastl/5872/74","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Migration from custom container library to augmented EASTL","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":35945,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-10T16:07:50.056Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eNot really other ideas, but I thought of the default shaders (ie. LitSolid) being quite monstrous and that it would have been nicer to have shader per purpose, like DiffuseTextured, NormalMappedTextured and possibly get rid of Techniques altogether at same time. Shaders could have then definitions (either automatically or manually) what requirements they have for textures / vertex input streams.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-10T18:31:40.927Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":61,"readers_count":60,"score":67.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5916,"topic_slug":"improving-the-render-pipeline","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":3}],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":35954,"name":"Eugene Kozlov","username":"Eugene","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/eugene/{size}/902_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-11T08:43:15.989Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"cadaver\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"5916\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/40/3_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e cadaver:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ebut I thought of the default shaders (ie. LitSolid) being quite monstrous and that it would have been nicer to have shader per purpose, like DiffuseTextured, NormalMappedTextured and possibly get rid of Techniques altogether at same time\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHow would you avoid copy-paste in such shaders?\u003cbr\u003e\nEven if you extract everything into functions‚Ä¶ Well, we already extracted pretty much everything into functions. And LitSolid is still quite huge. Shall we split it, there would be a lot of repeating lines in all variations.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt‚Äôs also not clear what configuration deserves separate shader and what configuration shall be just a define. How many variations should spawn from just LitSolid?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-11T08:43:29.252Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":52,"readers_count":51,"score":15.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":5916,"topic_slug":"improving-the-render-pipeline","display_username":"Eugene Kozlov","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Core developer","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":484,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":35955,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2020-02-11T11:40:30.187Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI think, using utility functions where possible.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, I see how shaders are split more as a content choice, the engine shouldn‚Äôt need to mandate it either way, just be able to configure whatever it wants out of the shader (like the light type or shadowing on/off). Ideally I always saw whatever Urho included just as an example shader, and the user writing their real shaders \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHaving deferred / forward embedded in same material or shader is also potentially cumbersome no matter how you look at it.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2020-02-11T11:40:30.187Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":52,"readers_count":51,"score":25.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":5916,"topic_slug":"improving-the-render-pipeline","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"user_id":3,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false}],"stream":[35925,35940,35942,35945,35954,35955]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,1017],[5,1016]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":7218,"title":"Jolt Physics: physics engine from Horizon Forbidden West open-sourced","fancy_title":"Jolt Physics: physics engine from Horizon Forbidden West open-sourced","slug":"jolt-physics-physics-engine-from-horizon-forbidden-west-open-sourced","posts_count":4,"reply_count":1,"highest_post_number":4,"image_url":null,"created_at":"